The paper deals with coding theory and properties of self-dual codes, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. The use of automorphisms and module theory suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the algebraic combinatorics (cs.CC) and group theory (cs.GT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses criteria for determining if a code is projective, which may be of interest to researchers in the cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category.
